ntend Svelte/SvelteKit\n│   ├── app.html                   # Root HTML template (French, no head content)\n│   ├── app.css                    # Global styles (TailwindCSS 4 + custom theme)\n│   ├── app.d.ts                   # Global TypeScript definitions\n│   ├── lib/\n│   │   ├── index.ts               # (empty, for imports)\n│   │   ├── components/\n│   │   │   └── Sidebar.svelte      # Navigation sidebar (6 main routes)\n│   │   ├── stores/\n│   │   │   ├── db.ts              # Database abstraction (getDb, query, execute)\n│   │   │   ├── accounts.ts         # Account store (CRUD, balance calc)\n│   │   │   ├── transactions.ts     # Transaction store (CRUD, search, filters, categorization)\n│   │   │   └── budget.ts           # Budget store (series, monthly budgets, aggregation)\n│   │   ├── types/\n│   │   │   └── index.ts            # TypeScript types (Account, Transaction, BudgetSeries, etc.)\n│   │   └── utils/\n│   │       └── format.ts           # Format helpers (currency, date, month, labels, colors)\n│   └── routes/\n│       ├── +page.svelte            # Root page (redirects to /dashboard)\n│       ├── +page.ts                # Redirect logic\n│       ├── +layout.svelte          # Main layout (Sidebar + main content area)\n│       ├── +layout.ts              # Route config (prerender, ssr)\n│       ├── dashboard/\n│       │   └── +page.svelte        # Dashboard (4 summary cards, accounts list, recent transactions, budget overview)\n│       ├── accounts/\n│       │   └── +page.svelte        # Accounts page (CRUD modal, total balance display)\n│       ├── transactions/\n│       │   └── +page.svelte        # Transactions page (table, search, filters, inline categorization)\n│       ├── budget/\n│       │   └── +page.svelte        # Budget page (monthly view with nav, series CRUD, inline budget editing)\n│       ├── analysis/\n│       │   └── +page.svelte        # Analysis page (placeholder, ready for charts)\n│       └── projects/\n│           └── +page.svelte        # Projects page (placeholder, ready for implementation)\n├── src-tauri/                     # Rust backend\n│   ├── Cargo.toml                 # Dependencies (tauri, sqlx, tauri-plugin-sql, chrono, serde)\n│   ├── src/\n│   │   ├── main.rs                # Entry point (calls app_lib::run())\n│   │   ├── lib.rs                 # App library setup (Tauri builder, DB migrations, plugins, IPC handlers)\n│   │   ├── commands.rs            # Tauri commands (only greet() function, template ready)\n│   │   └── db.rs                  # Database migrations (loads SQL from files)\n│   ├── migrations/\n│   │   └── 001_initial_schema.sql # Complete DB schema (14 tables, indexes, FK constraints)\n│   ├── build.rs                   # Tauri build script\n│   └── capabilities/\n│       └── default.json           # Security capabilities (SQL plugin permissions)\n├── static/\n│   └── favicon.svg                # App icon\n├── package.json                   # Frontend dependencies\n├── tsconfig.json                  # TypeScript strict mode\n├── vite.config.ts                 # Vite config (Tauri dev server setup)\n├── svelte.config.js               # SvelteKit static adapter config\n└── CLAUDE.md                      # Project specification (French, detailed brief)\n```\n\n---\n\n### Database Schema\n\n**14 tables** designed for a complete personal budget management system:\n\n1. **accounts** — Bank accounts (checking, savings, credit card, cash) with initial balances\n2. **budget_series** — Budget categories (income, recurring, variable, extras, savings, transfers)\n3. **sub_series** — Subcategories within budget series\n4. **transactions** — Individual transactions with categorization and import batch tracking\n5. **transaction_splits** — Split a transaction across multiple categories\n6. **monthly_budget** — Monthly budget amounts per series (planned vs actual)\n7. **recurring_transactions** — Templates for recurring transactions with frequency\n8. **projects** — Savings goals/projects with target amounts and dates\n9. **project_items** — Line items within projects\n10. **tags** — Transversal tags for transactions\n11. **transaction_tags** — Mapping between transactions and tags\n12. **categorization_rules** — Auto-categorization pattern matching (learns from manual categorization)\n13. **import_batches** — Metadata for imported transactions (OFX, QIF, CSV)\n\n**Indexes** on: date, account, series, fitid, period (year/month), project\n\n**Constraints:** Foreign keys with cascading deletes, unique compound keys, check constraints on enums\n\n---\n\n### Frontend Pages Built (5/6 MVP Pages Complete)\n\n#### **1. Dashboard** (/dashboard) — FULLY FUNCTIONAL\n- 4 summary cards: Total balance, Monthly income, Monthly expenses, Transaction count\n- Accounts list with individual balances\n- Last 10 transactions\n- Budget overview for current month (progress bars)\n- Data loaded from stores on mount\n\n#### **2. Accounts** (/accounts) — FULLY FUNCTIONAL\n- List all active accounts with balances (sorted by name)\n- Total balance display at top\n- CRUD modal (add/edit/delete accounts)\n- Account type labels (French: \"Compte courant\", \"Livret d'épargne\", etc.)\n- Edit and delete buttons inline\n\n#### **3. Transactions** (/transactions) — FULLY FUNCTIONAL\n- Table view of last 500 transactions (sortable date DESC)\n- Search by label (LIKE query)\n- Filters by account and category/series\n- Inline categorization dropdown (popover)\n- Add/edit/delete transactions via modal\n- Auto-categorization rule learning (stores matching patterns)\n- Shows account name, series name, amount (colored green/red)\n\n#### **4. Budget** (/budget) — FULLY FUNCTIONAL\n- Monthly view with prev/next navigation\n- Creates/edits budget series (categories) with budget area assignment\n- Inline editing of monthly budget amounts (save on blur/enter)\n- Progress bars showing actual vs planned (color-coded: green < 80%, yellow 80-100%, red > 100%)\n- Grouped display by budget area\n- Summary totals: Planned, Actual, Remaining\n- Delete button for series\n\n#### **5. Analysis** (/analysis) — PLACEHOLDER\n- Skeleton page (ready for charts with Chart.js or Layercake)\n- Shows \"No data yet\" message\n\n#### **6. Projects** (/projects) — PLACEHOLDER\n- Skeleton page (ready for savings goals)\n- Shows \"No projects\" message\n\n---\n\n### State Management (Svelte Stores)\n\n**4 Reactive Store Classes** using Svelte 5 `$state` runes:\n\n1. **accountStore** (src/lib/stores/accounts.ts)\n   - `accounts: Account[]`\n   - `loading`, `error` states\n   - Methods: `load()`, `create()`, `update()`, `remove()`\n   - Computed: `totalBalance`\n\n2. **transactionStore** (src/lib/stores/transactions.ts)\n   - `transactions: Transaction[]` (with joined account/series names)\n   - `search`, `filterAccountId`, `filterSeriesId` (reactive filters)\n   - Methods: `load()`, `create()`, `update()`, `categorize()`, `remove()`\n   - Auto-categorization learning via `categorize()`\n\n3. **budgetStore** (src/lib/stores/budget.ts)\n   - `series: BudgetSeries[]`, `monthlyBudgets`, `budgetLines` (aggregated)\n   - `year`, `month` (navigation state)\n   - Methods: `loadBudgetView()`, `loadSeries()`, `createSeries()`, `updateSeries()`, `removeSeries()`, `setMonthlyBudget()`\n   - Computed: `groupedByArea`, `totalPlanned`, `totalActual`\n   - Real-time aggregation of actual amounts from transactions\n\n4. **db** (src/lib/stores/db.ts)\n   - Database connection pooling\n   - `getDb()` — loads SQLite database (singleton)\n   - `query<T>()` — SELECT with typed results\n   - `execute()` — INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE\n\n---\n\n### UI/UX Design System\n\n**Dark Theme** (defined in app.css using TailwindCSS @theme):\n- **Primary**: #0f172a (very dark blue)\n- **Secondary**: #1e293b (dark blue)\n- **Card**: #1e293b\n- **Hover**: #334155\n- **Border**: #334155\n- **Text**: #f1f5f9 (white)\n- **Text Secondary**: #94a3b8 (gray)\n- **Text Muted**: #64748b (lighter gray)\n- **Accent**: #3b82f6 (bright blue)\n- **Success**: #22c55e (green)\n- **Warning**: #f59e0b (orange)\n- **Danger**: #ef4444 (red)\n- **Income**: #22c55e (green)\n- **Expense**: #ef4444 (red)\n\n**Components Used:**\n- Sidebar navigation with active state highlighting\n- Modal dialogs (fixed overlay with backdrop)\n- Tables with hover effects\n- Progress bars (budget tracking)\n- Inline buttons (edit/delete)\n- Summary cards with icon + metric\n- Form inputs and selects (with focus states)\n- Dropdown popovers (categorization)\n\n---\n\n### Backend Status\n\n**Minimal Implementation:**\n- `lib.rs` — Sets up Tauri builder with migrations and plugins\n- `commands.rs` — Only `greet()` function (template)\n- `db.rs` — Migrations loaded from SQL file\n- **No IPC commands yet** — All database access is currently from frontend via `tauri-plugin-sql` plugin\n\n**Database Path:** `sqlite:budgetview.db` (created at app startup)\n\n**Capabilities:** SQL plugin allows load, execute, select, close operations\n\n---\n\n### Key Completed Features (MVP Phase 1)\n\n1. ✅ **Database Schema** — Comprehensive, normalized, with migrations\n2. ✅ **Accounts Management** — CRUD with list view and balance tracking\n3. ✅ **Transactions** — CRUD, search, categorization with auto-learning\n4. ✅ **Budget Categories** — Create/edit/delete budget series\n5. ✅ **Monthly Budget Planner** — Set planned amounts, see actual vs planned with progress bars\n6. ✅ **Dashboard** — Overview with summaries, account list, recent transactions, budget snapshot\n7. ✅ **Data Formatting** — French localization (currency, dates, month names, labels)\n8. ✅ **Type Safety** — Full TypeScript types for all entities\n9. ✅ **Responsive UI** — TailwindCSS grid layouts, adaptive columns\n\n---\n\n### Not Yet Implemented (Phase 2 & 3)\n\n1. **Import** — OFX, QIF, CSV file parsing (Rust backend needed)\n2. **Charts** — Expense trends, pie charts by category (Chart.js integration)\n3. **Recurring Transactions** — Detection and templates\n4. **Projects** — Savings goal planning and tracking\n5. **Split Transactions** — Assigning transaction to multiple categories\n6. **Tauri IPC Commands** — Backend commands (only `greet()` exists)\n7. **Export** — PDF/CSV export\n8. **Encryption** — Password protection for database\n\n---\n\n### How It Works (Data Flow)\n\n1. **App Launch**: Tauri loads frontend (SvelteKit static), initializes SQLite via migration\n2. **Page Navigation**: Router loads Svelte page component, calls `onMount()`\n3. **Data Loading**: Store calls `query()` to fetch from SQLite (direct browser plugin access)\n4. **User Action**: Form submission triggers `create()`, `update()`, or `remove()` in store\n5. **Store Update**: Store executes SQL, reloads data, reactive state updates trigger re-render\n6. **UI Update**: Svelte reactivity ($state) updates components automatically\n\n**No Backend API Yet** — Frontend talks directly to SQLite via `@tauri-apps/plugin-sql`\n\n---\n\n### Known Limitations & Next Steps\n\n**Current Limitations:**\n- No file import (OFX/CSV)\n- No charts/analysis yet\n- No Tauri backend commands (all SQL from frontend)\n- No data export\n- No password/encryption\n- Analysis and Projects pages are stubs\n\n**Recommended Next Priority:**\n1. Implement file import (Rust backend command)\n2. Add charts to Analysis page\n3. Implement Projects functionality\n4. Add recurring transaction detection\n5. Test offline functionality and database persistence\n\n---\n\n### Absolute File Paths (Key Files)\n\n**Frontend Core:**\n- `/home/jeremy/Documents/budgetview-tauri/src/routes/+layout.svelte` — Main layout\n- `/home/jeremy/Documents/budgetview-tauri/src/routes/dashboard/+page.svelte` — Dashboard\n- `/home/jeremy/Documents/budgetview-tauri/src/routes/accounts/+page.svelte` — Accounts\n- `/home/jeremy/Documents/budgetview-tauri/src/routes/transactions/+page.svelte` — Transactions\n- `/home/jeremy/Documents/budgetview-tauri/src/routes/budget/+page.svelte` — Budget\n- `/home/jeremy/Documents/budgetview-tauri/src/lib/stores/db.ts` — DB abstraction\n- `/home/jeremy/Documents/budgetview-tauri/src/lib/stores/accounts.ts` — Account store\n- `/home/jeremy/Documents/budgetview-tauri/src/lib/stores/transactions.ts` — Transaction store\n- `/home/jeremy/Documents/budgetview-tauri/src/lib/stores/budget.ts` — Budget store\n- `/home/jeremy/Documents/budgetview-tauri/src/lib/types/index.ts` — Type definitions\n- `/home/jeremy/Documents/budgetview-tauri/src/lib/utils/format.ts` — Formatting utilities\n\n**Backend:**\n- `/home/jeremy/Documents/budgetview-tauri/src-tauri/src/lib.rs` — Tauri setup\n- `/home/jeremy/Documents/budgetview-tauri/src-tauri/src/commands.rs` — IPC commands\n- `/home/jeremy/Documents/budgetview-tauri/src-tauri/src/db.rs` — Migrations\n- `/home/jeremy/Documents/budgetview-tauri/src-tauri/migrations/001_initial_schema.sql` — DB schema\n\n**Config:**\n- `/home/jeremy/Documents/budgetview-tauri/package.json` — Frontend deps\n- `/home/jeremy/Documents/budgetview-tauri/src-tauri/Cargo.toml` — Rust deps\n- `/home/jeremy/Documents/budgetview-tauri/vite.config.ts` — Vite config\n- `/home/jeremy/Documents/budgetview-tauri/tsconfig.json` — TypeScript config\n- `/home/jeremy/Documents/budgetview-tauri/src/app.css` — Styling (dark theme)\n\n---\n\n### Summary: What's Working\n\nThe project is in **excellent MVP shape** with a solid foundation:\n\n✅ Full database schema with proper normalization  \n✅ All 5 main pages (dashboard, accounts, transactions, budget, analysis structure)  \n✅ Complete CRUD operations for accounts, transactions, and budget categories  \n✅ Reactive state management with Svelte 5 runes  \n✅ French localization throughout UI  \n✅ Dark modern design with TailwindCSS 4  \n✅ Type-safe TypeScript throughout  \n✅ Responsive layout (Sidebar + main content)  \n✅ Auto-learning categorization rules  \n✅ Monthly budget with actual vs planned comparison  \n\nThe frontend is nearly complete; the main gap is the backend (Rust commands) for file import and more complex business logic. The project is ready to move into Phase 2 (charts, imports, recurring transactions)."}],"totalDurationMs":164600,"totalTokens":61635,"totalToolUseCount":40,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":546,"cache_read_input_tokens":56643,"output_tokens":4445,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":546},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
